<ol><li>Because it has the&nbsp;<b>same length</b>&nbsp;and therefore&nbsp;<b>same time period</b>&nbsp;as the driver pendulum.</li><li>Its&nbsp;<b>natural frequency</b>&nbsp;is the same as the natural frequency of the driver.</li><li>So it&nbsp;<b>oscillates in resonance</b>&nbsp;with the driver because it is subjected to forced oscilltaions&nbsp;<b>of the same frequency as its own natural frequency</b>&nbsp;of oscillations.</li></ol>